The person, was not identified publicly, was discovered to have variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob Disease (vCJD), which causes personality change, loss of body function, brain deterioration and eventually death, officials from the health ministry said.
The cow was born in Shikaoi, north Japan's Hokkaido region, in October 2000, and was checked for mad cow disease after it died, the ministry said.
The EU said the program was one of 82 programs tackling 10 major animal diseases, including rabies, mad cow, and scrapie, a similar brain-wasting disease found in sheep.
